Sticks and Stones, the third record from Florida emo-punkers New Found Glory, might wear its broken heart on its sleeve, but that doesn&#039;t mean it has to pretend to be mature. No, Blink 182&#039;s first choice of support band have a firm grasp of the puerile: Sticks and Stones churns out dumb punk thrills at such a breakneck pace, you&#039;d swear they were going out of fashion. The chugging "It&#039;s Been A Summer" does Blink as well as Travis, Mark and Tom do themselves, while "Head On Collision" displays the group&#039;s tender emo side, frontman Jordan Pundik smarting at a vicious relationship spat. "It feels like I&#039;m bruised and broken / From our head on collision", he sobs, as guitars crunch and blunder madly in the background.

Enjoy! :)
